/ref>\n|  full member\n|}\n\n===WFIS South-East Asia===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" border=\"1\"\n|-\n! Country\n! Group\n|-\n| [[Scouting and Guiding in Bangladesh|Bangladesh]]\n| Independent Scouts of Bangladesh\n|-\n| [[Scouting and Guiding in mainland China|China]]\n| Shanghai Scout Association\n|-\n| [[Scouting in Korea|South Korea]]\n| Third Eye Scouting Association\n|-\n|rowspan=3| [[Scouting and Guiding in Pakistan|Pakistan]]\n| Independent Scouts of Pakistan\n|-\n| Nankana Sab Scout Organization\n|-\n| ADABKADA Scout Association\n|-\n| [[Scouting and Guiding in Sri Lanka|Sri Lanka]]\n| Independent Scouts of Sri Lanka\n|-\n|rowspan=2| [[Scouting and Guiding in the United Arab Emirates|United Arab Emirates]]\n| United Arab Emirates Independent Scout Association\n|-\n| Dubai Scout Organization\n|}\n\n==Jamborees and international camps==\n\n{{Main|World Federation of Independent Scouts World Jamboree}}\n\nWFIS has held World Jamborees in 2002, 2007, and 2011.\n\nIn addition to World Jamborees, the WFIS also regularly host regional international camps, such as Eurocamp. The following camps having taken place or are scheduled:\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Event !! Location, Country !! Theme !! Dates\n|-\n| 2006 || Eurocamp 2006 || [[Switzerland]] || ||\n|-\n| 2010 || Eurocamp 2010 || [[Germany]] || ||\n|-\n| 2014 || Eurocamp 2014 || [[Italy]] || ||\n|-\n| 2018 || [http://eurocamp18.com/ Eurocamp 2018] || [[Newbury, Berkshire]], [[United Kingdom]] || Lifelong friendships created by Scouting || 28 July to 4 August 2018\n|}\n\nWFIS also hosts a Jamboree On The Internet:\n* WFIS-JOTI 2010, hosted by WFIS Africa<ref>http://joti.wfis-africa.org/ WFIS-JOTI 2010</ref>\n\nMember Associations also regularly invite each other to their own camps, examples including:\n* The Baden-Powell Scouts' Association 2007 Centenary Camp\n* [[Jamboree 2008 (Northumberland)]]\n\n==International Scout Fellowship==\n{{Infobox WorldScouting\n| type = Organization\n| name = International Scout Fellowship\n| image = International Scout Fellowship.svg\n| imagesize = 90px\n| caption =\n| headquarters =\n| location =\n| country = Worldwide\n| f-date = 2007-08-01\n| founder =\n| award-for =\n| members =\n| website ={{URL|https://isf-world.org/}}\n}}\nThe International Scout Fellowship is an affiliate of WFIS, but not a member.\nIt is open to former and current adult members of WFIS, to other adult friends of Independent Scouting who wish to contribute to independent Scouting, regardless of their Scouting backgrounds.\n\nThe ISF is governed by its World Council which is composed of representatives of each member Chapter.  It meets once a year, usually electronically.  Its day-to-day affairs are directed by the Executive Committee, which is elected by the World Council.\n\nAll positions in the ISF are staffed by volunteers.  There are no paid employees.\n\n===Uniform===\nThe badge is that of the WFIS in reverse colours.\nThere is no set uniform of the ISF.  Member chapters determine their own uniforms with the badge of the ISF. Other chapters may use casual dress such as T-shirts, etc.\n\nThe emphasis of the ISF is on tangible results in supporting Independent Scouting associations, not on formalities.\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Portal:Scouting | The Scouting Portal ]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.wfis-worldwide.org/start.html WFIS Worldwide]\n{{-}}\n{{scouting|international}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:World Federation Of Independent Scouts}}\n[[Category:International Scouting organizations]]\n[[Category:Non-aligned Scouting organizations]]\n[[Category:Organizations established in 1996]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2014}}\n{{Infobox WorldScouting\n| type = Organization\n| name = World Federation of Independent Scouts\n| image = World Federation of Independent Scouts.svg\n| imagesize = 90px\n| caption =\n| headquarters =\n| location =\n| country = Worldwide\n| f-date = 1996\n| founder = [[Lawrie Dring]]\n| award-for =\n| chiefscouttitle =President\n| chiefscout =Klaus Tegeder\n| owner =\n| website ={{URL|https://wfis.world/}}\n}}\nThe '''World Federation of Independent Scouts''' (WFIS) is a [[non-governmental organization|non-governmental]] international [[Scouting]] organization with 82 affiliated Scout organizations in 41 countries. The affiliate Scout organizations collectively had an estimated 200,000 members in 3562 [[Scout Group]]s in 2010.<ref name= \"WFIS World Council Report 2010\">[http://www.gevitoria.com.br/World_Federation_of_Independent_Scouts_Report2011.pdf WFIS World Council Report 2010]</ref>  WFIS was formed in [[Laubach]], [[Germany]], in 1996 by [[Lawrie Dring]], a British Scouter with the independent [[Baden-Powell Scouts|Baden-Powell Scouts' Association]] (BPSA).\n\nThe World Federation of Independent Scouts is open to any Scouting association that is not affiliated with another international organization. WFIS requires that member associations \"follow, and use, Baden-Powell's original program, traditions, uniforms, morals, ethics, and structure as laid out in Baden-Powell's ''[[Scouting for Boys]]'',\" amended only for \"health, environmental, first-aid, and safety reasons.\"\n\nThe current President of the WFIS World Council is Klaus Tegeder, who was elected for a five-year term in 2007 and reelected in 2012 and 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.wfis-worldwide.org/wordpress/|title=WFIS WORLD COUNCIL|access-date=25 July 2019}}</ref> He is the former President of WFIS-Europe and still leads a German Scout troop.\n\n==WFIS Worldwide Committee==\nThe '''WFIS Worldwide Committee''' is the chief executive body of the World Federation of Independent Scouts and is composed of elected volunteers.  WFIS-Worldwide acts as an umbrella association for each of the regional Scout organisations.\n\n===Current members of the WFIS Worldwide Committee<ref>[http://www.wfis-worldwide.org/committee.html WFIS Worldwide Committee]</ref>===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! style=\"background:#efefef;\" | Name\n! style=\"background:#efefef;\" | Position\n|-\n|Klaus Tegeder\n|President\n|-\n|Fabian Figueroa\n|Vice-President\n|-\n|Silvana Silva Mauriello\n|Secretary\n|-\n|Per Stigaard\n|Treasurer\n|-\n|Marc Bruyneel\n|Wood Beads (Wood Badge) Coordinator\n|-\n|}\n\n==Regional divisions==\nThe WFIS is divided into eight regions:<ref>[http://www.wfis-worldwide.org/wordpress/?page_id=23 Regional Councils]</ref>\n* Africa\n* Asia\n* South East Asia\n* Europe\n* Middle East Region\n* America\n*\n\nThe Asian Region and Middle East Region are currently inactive, although there are WFIS Associations operating there.\n\n==List of members==\nIncluding prospected members\n\n===WFIS Africa===\n5860 members in 2010<ref name= \"WFIS World Council Report 2010\"/>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" border=\"1\"\n|-\n! Country\n! Group\n! Membership status\n|-\n| Congo Brazzaville\n| Eclaireurs Eclaireuses La\u00efque du Congo\n| prospect member\n|-\n| Ghana\n| Baden Powell Scouts of Africa\n| prospect member\n|-\n|rowspan=4|Ivory Coast\n|Association des Eclaireurs et Eclaaireuses Evang\u00e9liques de C\u00f4te d'Ivoire\n| prospect member\n|-\n|Baden Powell Scouts of Africa\n| prospect member\n|-\n|Scouts d'Afrique de C\u00f4te d'Ivoire\n| prospect member\n|-\n|Scouts Unitaires de C\u00f4te d'Ivoire\n| prospect member\n|-\n| Kenya\n| Baden Powell Scouts Association\n| prospect member\n|-\n|Nigeria\n|Baden Powell Scout Association, Nigeria\n|Full member{{citation needed|date=October 2019}}\n|}\n\n===WFIS Asia===\n155,303 members in 2010<ref name= \"WFIS World Council Report 2010\"/>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" border=\"1\"\n|-\n! Country\n! Group\n! Membership status\n|-\n|rowspan=6| [[Scouting and Guiding in India|India]]\n| [[The Scouts/Guides Organisation (India)|The Scouts/Guides Organisation]]<ref>[http://www.thescouts.co.in/ The Scouts/Guide Organisation of India]</ref>\n| full member\n|-\n| Hindustan Scouts and Guides Association<ref>[http://hsga.webnode.com/ Hindustan Scouts and Guides Association]</ref>\n| full member\n|-\n| Scout Bharti<ref>[https://scoutbharti.weebly.com Scout Bharti]</ref>\n| full member\n|-\n|Shriram Bajpai Scouts & Guides Organisations\n| full member\n|-\n|Federation of India for Sports, Scouting and Education<ref>[https://fisse.org.in Federation Of India For Sports, Scouting And Education]</ref>   \n|Prospect Member\n|-\n|Future Scouts & guides\n|Prospect Member {{citation needed|date=September 2019}}\n|-\n| [[Scouting in Japan|Japan]]\n| Independent  Scouts of Japan\n| prospect member\n|-\n|rowspan=2| [[Scouting in Nepal|Nepal]]\n|Metro Scouts Nepal <ref>[http://metroscouts.blogspot.com Metro Scouts Nepal]</ref>\n| prospect member\n|-\n|Nepal Independent Scouts Association<ref>[http://nepalindependentscouts.cms4people.com/ Nepal Independent Scouts Association]</ref>\n| prospect member\n|}\n\n===WFIS Europe===\n10,834 members in 2010<ref name= \"WFIS World Council Report 2010\"/>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Country\n! Group\n! Membership Status\n|-\n| [[Scouting and Guiding in Austria|Austria]]\n| Scouts of Europa\n| full member\n|-\n| [[Scouting and Guiding in Belgium|Belgium]]\n| Onafhankelijke Scouts en Gidsen - Scouts et Guides Ind\u00e9pendants\n| full member\n|-\n| rowspan=3 | [[Scouting and Guiding in the Czech Republic|Czech Republic]]\n| Skaut - \u010cesk\u00fd skauting ABS\n| full member\n|-\n| Svaz skautu a skautek Ceske Republiky\n| full member\n|-\n| Skaut SSV<ref name=\"WFIS-E\">[http://www.wfis-europe.org/wordpress/?page_id=35 WFIS-EUROPE Prospective Members]</ref>\n| prospect member\n|-\n| [[Scouting and Guiding in Denmark|Denmark]]\n| [[De Gule Spejdere i Danmark \u2013 Baden-Powell spejderne]]<ref>[http://www.gulspejder.dk/ Baden-Powell Scouts of Denmark]</ref>\n| full member\n|-\n| [[Scouting and Guiding in France|France]]\n| [[Chavagnes International College#Scouts de Chavagnes|Scouts de Chavagnes]]\n| full member\n|-\n| rowspan=16| [[Scouting and Guiding in Germany|Germany]]\n